1
00:00:07,340 --> 00:00:10,969
Teacher.

2
00:00:12,470 --> 00:00:16,016
Can’t you just live at our place?

3
00:00:17,851 --> 00:00:20,186
I really…

4
00:00:20,186 --> 00:00:23,857
I think I’d be fine as long as I have you.

5
00:00:59,434 --> 00:01:02,729
Hey, what’s going on between you two?

6
00:01:05,148 --> 00:01:07,817
You’re seriously suffocating me.

7
00:01:08,902 --> 00:01:11,613
I’ll go to the restroom.

8
00:01:29,714 --> 00:01:32,884
Hey, did you do something to Jeong-yeon?

9
00:01:34,761 --> 00:01:36,888
No?

10
00:01:37,514 --> 00:01:39,933
Really?

11
00:01:41,184 --> 00:01:44,729
But hey, Jeong-yeon’s experiment results—

12
00:01:44,729 --> 00:01:46,397
don’t you think they’re off?

13
00:01:46,397 --> 00:01:50,151
How do you even get a 99?

14
00:01:50,151 --> 00:01:51,486
That makes no sense.

15
00:01:51,486 --> 00:01:53,822
Look.

16
00:01:53,822 --> 00:01:56,574
I’m telling you, this is my first time seeing this.

17
00:02:03,081 --> 00:02:04,666
I’ll head out first.

18
00:02:04,666 --> 00:02:06,042
I’m leaving.

19
00:02:06,042 --> 00:02:08,628
Text me. Text me.

20
00:02:09,457 --> 00:02:12,875
[Myung-jin: Looking at the results, it’s 100%—
he’s got someone he likes right now lol]

21
00:02:12,876 --> 00:02:14,876
[Myung-jin: Ask who it is lol]

22
00:02:24,936 --> 00:02:29,732
Please say it’s my teacher.
That person.

23
00:02:33,403 --> 00:02:38,158
That experiment you said you saw seven years ago—

24
00:02:44,581 --> 00:02:48,835
you’re right. I used you.

25
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:53,464
A rich kid hanging out with bad friends—

26
00:02:53,464 --> 00:02:55,842
it’s a cliché.

27
00:02:59,554 --> 00:03:01,347
So what?

28
00:03:03,641 --> 00:03:06,060
Because of that, I got my act together.

29
00:03:06,644 --> 00:03:09,439
Sure, I repeated a year, but—

30
00:03:09,439 --> 00:03:13,026
I got into a good university.
That means it worked, right?

31
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:22,869
For you,
and for me.

32
00:03:23,411 --> 00:03:25,079
Jeong-yeon…

33
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:32,003
It’s just that I feel guilty.

34
00:03:43,348 --> 00:03:44,682
So—

35
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:49,979
that’s why I came back, all grown up.

36
00:04:15,964 --> 00:04:19,175
Put that on.

37
00:04:19,175 --> 00:04:22,136
Let’s run the final experiment.

38
00:04:30,728 --> 00:04:34,732
Case-Delphi.
We will proceed with the next question.

39
00:04:36,901 --> 00:04:39,612
About the other person—

40
00:04:39,612 --> 00:04:43,616
tell me what you’ve already come to like.

41
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:47,662
At first,

42
00:04:47,662 --> 00:04:50,373
I liked him because he was handsome.

43
00:04:50,373 --> 00:04:52,917
And because he was kind.

44
00:04:55,586 --> 00:04:59,966
I liked how cold he could be,
almost frighteningly so, when he was firm.

45
00:04:59,966 --> 00:05:02,635
I liked that he tried to keep boundaries.

46
00:05:07,849 --> 00:05:10,310
But the best part—

47
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:16,065
was finding out he’d been watching over me
this whole time.

48
00:05:16,065 --> 00:05:19,610
I liked that more than I could bear.

49
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:35,710
Is there—

50
00:05:37,712 --> 00:05:41,215
even as a joke—

51
00:05:41,215 --> 00:05:45,803
something you should never say?

52
00:05:47,138 --> 00:05:50,350
Actually, it was all a lie.

53
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:53,227
I never liked you.

54
00:05:54,354 --> 00:05:56,314
If tonight—

55
00:05:57,940 --> 00:06:04,697
you were to die without contacting anyone—

56
00:06:05,823 --> 00:06:08,993
of all the things you didn’t get to say,

57
00:06:08,993 --> 00:06:14,957
what would you regret the most?

58
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:17,335
And—

59
00:06:19,295 --> 00:06:24,634
who would you want to say it to?

60
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:27,887
I like you.

61
00:06:27,887 --> 00:06:29,222
Hyung

62
00:06:41,317 --> 00:06:44,695
This is the final question.

63
00:06:48,574 --> 00:06:51,911
Open up about your condition,

64
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:55,331
and ask the other person for advice.

65
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:58,209
Before—

66
00:07:00,044 --> 00:07:04,132
when I found that experiment notebook—

67
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:07,760
I was angry, thinking you had deceived me.

68
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:15,643
But—

69
00:07:21,065 --> 00:07:24,444
when I thought about how you’d been watching me
all this time—

70
00:07:28,448 --> 00:07:30,491
I liked that, too.

71
00:07:38,082 --> 00:07:41,127
I’m kind of strange, right?

72
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:43,254
I still am.

73
00:07:44,213 --> 00:07:48,009
I don’t mind if I’m just a test subject.

74
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:50,803
I don’t mind if you use me.

75
00:07:53,181 --> 00:07:58,019
I just want you to like me.

76
00:07:59,312 --> 00:08:02,482
I really—

77
00:08:02,482 --> 00:08:05,735
I like you so, so much.

78
00:08:23,419 --> 00:08:26,255
(Finally)

79
00:08:27,590 --> 00:08:30,635
(the experiment is over)

80
00:08:36,766 --> 00:08:39,644
Hey, but that experiment you’re doing with Jeong-yeon—

81
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:41,896
are you even reporting it to the company?

82
00:08:41,896 --> 00:08:44,774
That’s the experiment we did back in undergrad.

83
00:08:44,774 --> 00:08:48,569
(How do you even get a 99 for Jeong-yeon’s results?
That makes no sense.)

84
00:08:48,569 --> 00:08:49,904
(Are you seeing someone right now?)

85
00:08:49,904 --> 00:08:52,114
As you exchange questions back and forth,

86
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:54,242
(It was my most precious memory.)

87
00:08:54,242 --> 00:08:58,079
at some point, you end up confessing even your real feelings,

88
00:08:58,079 --> 00:09:00,581
and by the time you get to the last question—

89
00:09:00,581 --> 00:09:02,083
(Do you still like me?)

90
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:05,378
you fall in love with each other.

91
00:09:05,378 --> 00:09:08,589
“Arthur Aron’s 36 Questions Experiment.”

92
00:09:08,589 --> 00:09:11,008
That’s it, right?

93
00:09:11,008 --> 00:09:13,636
Yes, Professor. How have you been?

94
00:09:13,636 --> 00:09:15,346
I’m calling because—

95
00:09:15,346 --> 00:09:16,764
about that assistant researcher

96
00:09:16,764 --> 00:09:19,016
I mentioned last time—

97
00:09:19,016 --> 00:09:21,602
they wrote a paper on self-control in at-risk youth.

98
00:09:21,602 --> 00:09:24,814
I found a paper written by someone like that.

99
00:09:24,814 --> 00:09:26,816
What do you think about them?

100
00:09:27,858 --> 00:09:29,193
Yes.

101
00:09:29,527 --> 00:09:32,113
Thank you.

102
00:10:01,058 --> 00:10:06,480
(Jeong-yeon… you…)

103
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:10,985
(you’ve become perfectly mine.)

104
00:10:56,614 --> 00:11:01,285
Name three things you have in common
with the other person.

105
00:11:01,285 --> 00:11:02,870
Hmm…

106
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:05,456
Good at studying?

107
00:11:05,456 --> 00:11:07,124
Only think about one person,

108
00:11:08,334 --> 00:11:10,878
and… admirable?

109
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:14,298
What is your most precious memory?

110
00:11:15,758 --> 00:11:18,844
The day I first met him.

111
00:11:18,844 --> 00:11:23,015
Back then, he was just a sweet kid
who looked like he needed help.

112
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:31,440
My experiment was meant to help someone like that.

113
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:42,743
But when I saw him come back all grown up—

114
00:11:42,743 --> 00:11:46,372
the results of the experiment
no longer mattered.

115
00:11:46,372 --> 00:11:51,752
What does a “perfect” day look like to you?

116
00:11:51,752 --> 00:11:54,588
The day—

117
00:11:54,588 --> 00:11:58,259
The day Jeong-yeon is entirely in my arms.

118
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:10,688
(I…)

119
00:12:10,688 --> 00:12:14,775
(I knew everything, teacher.)

120
00:12:20,698 --> 00:12:22,199
Me too.

121
00:12:24,326 --> 00:12:28,497
I like you too, Jeong-yeon.

122
00:12:29,749 --> 00:12:31,000
Me too, hyung.
